com.edatasource.receipts.parser

Class AbstractParser<T extends Receipt>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.edatasource.receipts.parser.AbstractParser<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractEcommerceParser, AbstractJsoupParser, AbstractReservationParser, AbstractSubscriptionParser 

    public abstract class AbstractParser<T extends Receipt>
extends java.lang.Object
    The base class that all the parsers must implement.

    In general, implementers will extend one of the higher-level parsers: AbstractEcommerceParser or AbstractSubscriptionParser

      • getReceiptSubType

        public java.lang.String getReceiptSubType()
        Returns the subcategory for the receipt type handled by this parser.

        Concrete (or higher-level abstarct) classes should override this method to set the sub-type for the receipt handled by the specific parser.
